alwaysApply: true
---

# Git commits

- Never add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or any other agent co-author trailer to commits.
- Never add `Co-authored-by`, `Co-Authored-By`, or similar attribution lines unless the user explicitly requests them.

# Prose style

- Never use the em dash character (U+2014) in this project.
- Prefer `:`, `,`, `;`, or a plain hyphen `-` when separating clauses.
- In docs that mention the rule, refer to "em dash" or U+2014 in prose; do not include the character as an example.
